{
  "texts": [
    "By focusing on object centric alignment, the model can overcome the problems of point clouds captured from different viewpoints, low overlapping point clouds, and the need to learn correspondence across the entire scene.",
    "Consistent Two-Flow Network (CTF-Net) is proposed by Yan et al. (2021).",
    "Considering that the completed shapes are easier to register than each shape individually, and the degree of overlap of the complete shapes increases, the registration becomes easier.",
    "Therefore, the method uses neural network to learn the prior knowledge of a class of objects and completes the shape completion.",
    "The main idea of this model is to train two independent networks jointly to complete the two tasks of nonoverlapping part shape complement and point cloud registration after compliment."
  ]
}